            <h3>Our Safety Standards & Practices</h3>
            <ul class="safety-list">
                <li><strong>OHSAS 18001 / ISO 45001 Certified</strong> ‚Äì Fully compliant with international occupational health & safety management systems</li>
                <li><strong>Mandatory Safety Training</strong> ‚Äì Every worker receives 40+ hours of annual safety training (including first aid, fire safety, working at heights, electrical hazards, and heavy machinery operation)</li>
                <li><strong>Full PPE Provision</strong> ‚Äì Hard hats, safety boots, high-visibility vests, gloves, harnesses, respirators, ear protection ‚Äî provided and enforced at all sites</li>
                <li><strong>Daily Safety Briefings & Audits</strong> ‚Äì Tool-box talks every morning + weekly site safety inspections by certified safety officers</li>
                <li><strong>Risk Assessments & Method Statements</strong> ‚Äì Every task is pre-assessed with detailed RAMS (Risk Assessment & Method Statement) approved before start</li>
                <li><strong>Incident Reporting & Near-Miss Culture</strong> ‚Äì Anonymous reporting system + rewards for reporting near-misses to prevent future incidents</li>
                <li><strong>Emergency Preparedness</strong> ‚Äì On-site first-aid stations, trained first-aiders, fire extinguishers, evacuation drills every quarter</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="safety-note">
                Safety is not just a policy ‚Äî it's our core value. We believe every worker should return home safely to their family every single day.
